relations.head: Sestrins
relations.label: interact with
relations.text: Sestrins, a family of poorly understood growth regulators (Sestrin1-Sestrin3), interact with GATOR2 in an amino-acid-sensitive fashion.

relations.head: GATOR2
relations.label: upregulate
relations.text: GATOR2 is a complex of unknown function that positively regulates mTORC1 signaling by acting upstream of or in parallel to GATOR1.

relations.head: GATOR1
relations.label: inhibit
relations.text: GATOR1, which is a GTPase-activating protein (GAP) for RagA or RagB and an inhibitor of the amino-acid-sensing pathway.

relations.head: amino acid
relations.label: activate
relations.text: A key input is amino acids, which act through the heterodimeric Rag GTPases (RagA or RagB bound to RagC or RagD) in order to promote the translocation of mTORC1 to the lysosomal surface, its site of activation.
